        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> When I nvim -u NORC and then lua vim.opt.shortmess:append {\"A\"}\r\n\r\nThat's invalid, it should be `append(\"A\")` (no table)\r\n\r\n> If I `lua vim.opt.shortmess = vim.opt.shortmess .. \"A\"`\r\n\r\nThat's also invalid, since `vim.opt.shortmess` is an object; to get the value, you need to explicitly use `vim.opt.shortmess:get()`. Please read `:h lua-guide` and  `:h vim.opt` carefully.\r\n",
